sql:
SELECT fuel_efficiency_year, MAX(highway_mpg) AS max_highway_mpg
FROM fuel_efficiency
GROUP BY fuel_efficiency_year;

external_knowledge:
- Average MPG (miles per gallon) is a measure of a vehicle's fuel efficiency; 
- Access frequency refers to the number of times a vehicle has been accessed in the past year;
- A vehicle model is considered "popular" if it has been accessed more than three times in the past year;
- Vehicle makes/models with multiple IDs are typically considered more reliable or widely used.

- 'at least four cylinders' refers to vehicles with four or more cylinders in their engines; 
- '2023 fuel efficiency data' means that the fuel efficiency of the vehicle was recorded in the year 2023; 
- 'accessed after September 30, 2023' means that the data for these vehicles was retrieved or recorded on or after October 1, 2023.
